cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence in the design and optimization of 6G networks, which involves network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes an AI-enabled architecture for 6G networks, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses data mining and analytics, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory). The intelligent control layer and smart application layer mentioned in the paper are related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper mentions applications such as virtual and augmented reality, which fall under the scope of cs.MM (Multimedia).
